                <p class="lead">Accidental damage is when something happens to your property that is completely out of your control. It's defined in our policy document as:</p>
                <p class="highlight-text">"Physical harm that impairs the normal function of your mobile phone."</p>
                <p class="lead">Examples of accidental damage:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Spillages</li>
                    <li>Damage by children</li>
                    <li>Damage caused by pets</li>
                    <li>Electrical surges</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="lead">What isn't covered:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cosmetic damage</li>
                    <li>Damage resulting from you putting your phone at risk</li>
                    <li>Damage caused before the insurance policy</li>
                    <li>Excess: You need to pay a contribution every time you make a successful claim.</li>
