                </button>
                <h3 class="modal-title text-center">Unauthorised Network Charges</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p class="lead">We cover you for up to &pound;1,000 of unauthorised network changes. Unauthorised usage applies when you have either lost your phone or had it stolen; and it is then used without your knowledge or permission. It’s defined in our policy document as:</p>
                <p class="highlight-text">"Unauthorised network charges (calls, texts, data) as a result of someone else using your mobile phone without consent"</p>
                <p class="lead">So, if your mobile phone has been used without your consent after it has been lost or stolen, we will pay those charges incurred for 24 hours from the time of Loss or Theft, as long as:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>You notify your network within 24 hours of the Theft/Loss </li>
                    <li>Your Loss or Theft claim for your mobile phone is approved </li>
                    <li>SIM card is registered to you or your family member, or to the business or an employee for these charges to be covered.</li>
                    <li>You provide the copy of an itemised bill</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{# End Unauthorised Network Charges #}

